The Condemnatio is, with very few exceptions, found in every formula, being the clause in which the iudex is instructed to condemn or absolve the defendant according to the truth or falsehood of the plaintiifs allegations. The formulary procedure provided no direct machinery for enforcing on a defendant delivery of specific property, or specific performance ol a contract, and consequently the gist of the condemnatio always lay in a money payment (Gaius iv. 48).
